        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qA1" data-parent="#faq">
        <div class="card card-body">
            <p>
                After purchasing a paid IRRISketch subscription, you need to activate it manually in your personal
                account
                at the link:
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://www.irrisketch.com/account/orders"
                   target="_blank">www.irrisketch.com/account/orders</a>,
            </p>
            where your subscription will be in the right column. After activation, you will be able to freely use all
            paid functionality of the service.
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qA2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="qA2">
            I paid for the subscription, but it did not appear in my personal cabinet.
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qA2" data-parent="#faq">
        <div class="card card-body">
            <p>
                In this case, you need to go to your personal account by following this link:
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://www.irrisketch.com/account/orders"
                   target="_blank">www.irrisketch.com/account/orders</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                Look at the button at the bottom of the order. The red "Repeat" button means that the payment
                failed
                and you should try again, but first check to see if the money has been charged.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you have been seeing the yellow "Payment in progress" button for a long time, chances are that the
                transaction has not
                happened
                automatic confirmation. If this is the case, click this button to complete it and everything should
                work.
            </p>
            After the successful payment and completion of the transaction you will see a green "Payment Verified"
            button.
            Click it and your subscription will appear in the right column.
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <div class="row mb-3">
        <div class="col-lg-12 text-center"><span class="h3">Questions about projects</span></div>
    </div>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qP1"
                aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qP1">
            Changes in the project have not been saved/I want to restore a certain state of
            project, what should I do?
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qP1" data-parent="#faq">
        <div class="card card-body">
            <p>
                1. Öffnen Sie denselben Browser auf demselben Computer, auf dem Sie zuletzt an dem Projekt gearbeitet haben.
            </p>
            <p>
                2. Gehen Sie zum IRRISketch-Workshop und öffnen Sie das Projekt, auf das sich das Problem bezieht.
            </p>
            <p>
                3. Wenn beim Öffnen eines Projekts ein Fenster erscheint, das anbietet, das Projekt wiederherzustellen, klicken Sie auf die Schaltfläche "Wiederherstellen" und sehen Sie sich das Ergebnis an. Wenn das Projekt nicht in den gewünschten Zustand wiederhergestellt wurde, folgen Sie den Anweisungen weiter.
            </p>
            <p>
                4. Klicken Sie in der oberen rechten Ecke auf die Schaltfläche "Verlauf" (Uhrsymbol mit Pfeil) und wenn alles korrekt gespeichert wurde, sehen Sie eine Liste der Zeitstempel Ihrer Projektzustände. Wählen Sie denjenigen aus, bei dem das Projekt in dem gewünschten Zustand war. Speichern Sie das Projekt danach unbedingt!
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qP2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="qP2">
            How do I display the grid in a project drawing? The drawing grid does not appear when outputting to PDF/PNG.
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qP2" data-parent="#faq">
        <div class="card card-body">
        <span>
            To display the grid when printing, it must be placed on the drawing as an image. You can download the grid,
            for example <a
                    href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PrKMoz9YDW-UHNwBpxTXMzGqLM-X3Mb_/view?usp=sharing"
                    target="_blank">from here</a>, and then scale it on the drawing to the desired size.
        </span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qP3"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="qP3">
            How do I transfer a project from one account to another?
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qP3" data-parent="#faq">
        <div class="card card-body">
            To do this, you can download the project file using the appropriate button on the top right panel
            After that, create an empty project on a new account and using the "Load" button, open previously downloaded
            file.
            <img src="/images/faq/downloadbuttonglobal.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="30%" height="30%">
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qP5"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="qP5">
            Project "hangs"/Transition to drawing mode takes a lot of time
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qP5" data-parent="#faq">
        <span>
            <p>
                Usually, this is related to a very large number of elements in the project, as IRRISketch Residential is not designed for particularly large plots. This problem can be solved by deleting all existing objects in drawing mode and replacing them with a single background.
            </p>
            <p>
                1. Create a copy of the project and open it if you're afraid of accidentally losing data.
            </p>
            <p>
                2. Switch to irrigation mode and use the ctrl+a key combination to select all elements, then cut them using the ctrl+x key combination (they will be saved in the clipboard).
            </p>
            <p>
                3. Switch to drawing mode, set the "Landscape" setting in the "Visual Style" tab to obtain the original landscape of the project, and remove the stamp.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/visualStyleEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="30%" height="30%">
            <p>
                4. Select a sheet format from A1 to A4. The larger the sheet size, the higher the quality of the final image, but the more space it will occupy.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/listFormatEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="30%" height="30%">
            <p>
                5. Use the "Ruler" tool in drawing mode to measure any easily measurable element of the drawing and record its length, as it will be needed later.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/rulerEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="50%" height="50%">
            <p>
                6. Switch to "Edit Drawing" mode at the bottom of the screen and insert the drawing into the sheet using the button at the bottom left. Export the project as an image.
                If the resulting image is larger than 10MB, you won't be able to use it. In that case, if you know how to use various image editors (such as Photoshop, Gimp), compress the image or reduce the number of colors. This will reduce the file size.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/fitEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="100%" height="100%">
            <p>
                7. Insert the image into the project and set the correct scale using the length recorded in step 5.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/resizeEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="50%" height="50%">
            <p>
                8. Align the image with your drawing so that all elements are in the same positions as they appear in the image.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/alignEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="50%" height="50%">
            <p>
                9. Lock the image by selecting it and clicking the corresponding button at the bottom left.
            </p>
            <img src="/images/faq/lockEN.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsive" alt="Download button"
                 width="15%" height="15%">
            <p>
                10. Use the ctrl+a key combination to select all elements in drawing mode and delete them. Only your image should remain.
            </p>
            <p>
                11. Return to irrigation mode and paste all previously deleted irrigation elements back onto the drawing using the ctrl+v key combination. If done correctly, all elements should return to their original positions.
            </p>
        </span>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qP5"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="qP5">
            In the drawing mode some zones are not displayed/the drip is not displayed
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qP5" data-parent="#faq">
        <span>
           This behaviour is related to the zone representation settings in the layout.
            To change the zone representation settings, in the lower left corner, in the layouts mode, click on the "Zones representation" button and check the boxes next to the zones you want to see in the layout. Alternatively, you can create a new layout and all existing zones will be displayed on it.
        </span>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <p>
        <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#qP6"
                aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qP6">
            Layoutbild ist nach dem Exportieren in PDF/Bild falsch gedreht/platziert
        </button>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="qP6" data-parent="#faq">
    <span>
        <p>
            Dies geschieht, weil Ihr Originalbild EXIF-Metadaten enthält. Um das Bild ordnungsgemäß zu verhalten, müssen Sie diese Metadaten entfernen, indem Sie den Dienst <a href="https://www.verexif.com/en/" target="_blank">www.verexif.com/en/</a> verwenden.
        </p>
        <p>
            Nachdem Sie den Link geöffnet haben - laden Sie Ihr Bild hoch, drücken Sie dann die Schaltfläche "EXIF entfernen", laden Sie das neue Bild herunter und ersetzen Sie das alte Bild in IRRISketch.
        </p>
    </span>
    </div>
    <hr>
</div>